        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 2:20PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 219 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles northwest of Currie, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Areas of blowing dust possible. Minor
damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southeastern Elko
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
